<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-5199] Avoid serializing to byte[] on commitlog append</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-5199</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We used to avoid re-serializing RowMutations by caching the byte[] that we read off the wire.  We don&apos;t do that anymore since we fixed MessagingService to not create intermediate byte[].  So we should serialize the mutation directly to the commitlog.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12629836">CASSANDRA-5199</key>
            <summary>Avoid serializing to byte[] on commitlog append</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
