                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13566141" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 30 Jan 2013 04:06:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;1.2 version just gets rid of the byte[] caching, since it&apos;s never actually re-used.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13566144" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 30 Jan 2013 04:09:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;2.0 version adds ByteBufferOutputStream and ChecksummedOutputStream to get rid of byte[] serialization entirely.  Also fixes mutation-length checksumming to include the entire length, not just the first eight bits.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13570513" author="yukim" created="Mon, 4 Feb 2013 19:06:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 for both.&lt;br/&gt;
nit: you need the license header to new files in 2.0.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
